The White House released a statement by Lisa O. Monaco, Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, on the anniversary of the Paris attacks. The statement expresses solidarity with France and highlights the ongoing fight against ISIL. It mentions the efforts of the United States and its partners in destroying ISIL and its false caliphate, strengthening local forces, conducting air strikes against ISIL leaders, and exchanging information to counter potential threats. The statement emphasizes the united front of the United States and France in dealing a lasting defeat to ISIL.